headline: Here's How Intel Could Be Affected by the United States' Rare Earths Trade With China
summary: China had restricted the export of rare earths in an escalation of the trade war with the U.S.  Rare earths are critical to the production of components found in data centers.  Intel's business could be adversely impacted should China decide to limit the export of rare earths.
